I'm currently working as a software engineer, which is also my dream job, and I'd love to share my journey with you.
I first learned about this career through an advertisement on Facebook. I was immediately attracted to the idea of building useful solutions using technology. After that, I decided to apply to a prestigious university in Ho Chi Minh City that specializes in Information Technology. Fortunately, I passed the national extrance exam with a high score and got accepted.
During my time at university, I gained hands-on experience with various technologies and frameworks. I also built a personal portfolio to showcase my skills. After graduating, I joined a local startup that focuses on optimizing farm operations, which gave me real-world experience in building products.
I would like to continue doing this job for as long as possible because I find it both challenging and rewarding. As a software engineer, I constantly need to learn new frameworks and improve my technical skills. At the same time, soft skills like communication and teamwork are equally important. Although the job can sometimes be stressful, especially when I have to learn many things at once, I find it very satisfying when users actually use my products and give positive feedback.
I would definitely recommend this job to people who are independent and curious about how things work. In my opinion, these qualities are essential for anyone who wants to grow and succeed in this field.
